NAME
     sleep - suspend execution for a given number of seconds

SYNOPSIS
     sleep seconds

EXAMPLES

     sleep 10            # Suspend execution for 10 sec.

DESCRIPTION

     The caller is suspended  for  the  indicated  number  of  seconds.   This
     command is typically used in shell scripts.

SEE ALSO
     sleep(3).



































